{"summary":"Generate Emacs TAGS file from Erlang source files","description":"<p> </p><p>A <span class=\"code\">TAGS</span> file is used by Emacs to find function and variable definitions in any source file in large projects. This module can generate a <span class=\"code\">TAGS</span> file from Erlang source files. It recognises functions, records, and macro definitions.</p> <p></p>","funcs":" <table class=\"func-table\"><tbody><tr class=\"func-tr\"><td class=\"func-td\"><div class=\"bold_code fun-type\"><span ><span id=\"ghlink-file-1-id91817\" class=\"ghlink\"><a href=\"/erldoc/docs/https://github.com/erlang/otp/edit/maint/lib/tools/doc/src/tags.xml#L44\" title=\"Found an issue with the documentation? Fix it by clicking here!\"><span class=\"pencil\"></span></a></span><a class=\"title_link\" name=\"file-1\" href=\"/erldoc/docs/#file-1\">file(File [, Options])</a></span></div></td><td class=\"func-since-td\"></td></tr></tbody></table><div class=\"REFBODY rb-7\"><p> </p><p>Create a <span class=\"code\">TAGS</span> file for the file <span class=\"code\">File</span>.</p> <p></p></div> <table class=\"func-table\"><tbody><tr class=\"func-tr\"><td class=\"func-td\"><div class=\"bold_code fun-type\"><span ><span id=\"ghlink-files-1-id91855\" class=\"ghlink\"><a href=\"/erldoc/docs/https://github.com/erlang/otp/edit/maint/lib/tools/doc/src/tags.xml#L51\" title=\"Found an issue with the documentation? Fix it by clicking here!\"><span class=\"pencil\"></span></a></span><a class=\"title_link\" name=\"files-1\" href=\"/erldoc/docs/#files-1\">files(FileList [, Options])</a></span></div></td><td class=\"func-since-td\"></td></tr></tbody></table><div class=\"REFBODY rb-7\"><p> </p><p>Create a TAGS file for the files in the list <span class=\"code\">FileList</span>.</p> <p></p></div> <table class=\"func-table\"><tbody><tr class=\"func-tr\"><td class=\"func-td\"><div class=\"bold_code fun-type\"><span ><span id=\"ghlink-dir-1-id91887\" class=\"ghlink\"><a href=\"/erldoc/docs/https: